cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the classification of fundus images for the diagnosis of glaucoma using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method of using class activation maps (CAM) as a mask filter, which involves machine learning techniques such as feature extraction and image processing, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for medical diagnosis also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with medical data and diagnosis, which suggests cs.MED (Medical Informatics) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves the use of image retrieval techniques, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
